    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "On Heroku, we can't add a local config `instance/config.py` that's not part of the repo. Instead, they support configuration through env vars. Document this pattern.\r\n\r\n`myapp/config.py`:\r\n\r\n~~~python\r\nMAIL_USERNAME = os.environ.get('FLASK_MAIL_USERNAME', 'default')\r\nLDAP_PORT = int(os.environ.get('FLASK_LDAP_PORT', 636))\r\n~~~",
